## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

**Recommended Voice:** Confident beauty editor — insider authority, not brand-neutral.

**Tone Characteristics:**
- Opinionated but evidence-backed (cite Fresha data and expert names, not just vibes)
- Warm and direct — writes to a reader who trusts your taste
- Light wit where appropriate ("florals for spring — groundbreaking" is fair game if subverted well)
- Decisive — no hedging on trend verdicts

**Language Style:** Use "you" directly. Avoid jargon without context (explain BIAB on first use). Short declarative sentences for trend verdicts. Analogies welcome (e.g. "quiet luxury has arrived at the nail salon"). British English if site standard applies.

**Audience Match:** Trend-aware women 18–38 who follow nail artists on Instagram/TikTok, visit salons regularly, and want editorial curation over an algorithmic mood board dump. They read Who What Wear and Refinery29 — they expect a point of view.

